The paper deals with authorship identification in emails, which is a natural language processing task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also employs feature selection techniques and classification algorithms, which are common in information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) research. Additionally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of the proposed model in detecting fraudulent emails, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR).
